channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: NEW: IDF Confirms It Took Out 2 Top Hamas Commanders in Airstrike on Rafah
‘Squad’ member Rashida Tlaib calls Biden ‘enabler’ of genocide at conference linked to terrorist group, CCP
item.description: Rashida Tlaib on Sunday spoke at a conference attended by a member of a designated terrorist organization and funded by an asset of the Chinese Communist Party (CCP).

item.title: RFK Jr. Quickly Eliminated From Libertarian Nomination
item.description: Independent Robert F. Kennedy Jr. was quickly eliminated in the first round of voting for presidential nominees at the Libertarian National Convention in Washington, D.C., on Sunday.

item.title: How Low Can You Go: Ana Navarro's Vile Remarks About Latino Trump Supporters
CBP nabs more Chinese illegal immigrants at California border
item.description: U.S. Customs and Border Protection on Saturday stopped nearly 120 Chinese illegal immigrants at California border, part of a growing trend at the San Diego sector since October.

item.title: Dip in Border Crossings Sparks Call for New Legislation
item.description: As election season heats up, lawmakers on opposite sides are stating that the reported dip in border crossings is not permanent and that Congress must pass legislation to continue the trend.

item.title: Seven Years Later, Marine Widow Recalls Trump Hugging Her Son at Husband's Arlington Grave
Presidential candidate Jill Stein slams DNC for posting, deleting ‘Third Party Project Manager’ job
item.description: Longshot Green Party presidential candidate Jill Stein slammed the Democratic National Committee Friday for posting, and then deleting, a job for monitoring third party candidates.

item.title: Rep. Waltz: GOP, Dem Vets Clean Vietnam Memorial Together
item.description: Rep. Michael Waltz, R-Fla., described to CBS News' "Face the Nation" on Sunday how he started a tradition of getting together members of Congress who are U.S. military veterans to help clean up the Vietnam Memorial in Washington, D.C., before every Memorial Day.

item.title: Philadelphia Couple Find Love, Get Married - at 102 and 100 Years of Age
NATO boss takes apparent swipe at Biden, argues to end restrictions on US weapons for Russian targets
item.description: NATO boss Jens Stoltenberg echoed calls for the U.S. to end restrictions on Ukraine's ability to use American weapons to strike targets inside of Russian territory.

item.title: Mass Migration Overwhelming Sanctuary City Schools
item.description: Mass migration is overwhelming American public schools and costing legal Americans public education services, school administrators are warning.

item.title: Buttigieg Flails Trying to Explain Why Only 8 EV Charging Stations Have Been Built by Biden Admin
Senator blasts federal parks officials for reportedly barring American flags in beloved national park
item.description: Sen. Dan Sullivan, R-Alaska, sent a letter to leaders of the National Park Service demanding answers on why an American flag was banned from Denali National Park.

item.title: Rep. Donalds Pushes Back on Claim He's a Trump 'Prop'
item.description: Rep. Byron Donalds Sunday slammed a television host who claimed former President Donald Trump was using him as a "prop" while he campaigned with him in the Bronx last week, saying her comments are "nothing more than crabs in a barrel."
